## No `else`

```js
'use strict';
// this is not allowed in JS! you will get a syntax error
//  it looks logical and useful, but does not exist

let input = null;
while (input === null) {
  input = prompt('enter something');
} else { // SyntaxError
  alert('canceling is not allowed');
}

alert(input);
```

